Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.56,0:00:18.91,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Amara...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.48,0:00:23.03,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever thought the wind felt good?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.03,0:00:23.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:25.70,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.22,0:00:28.46,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Having some morning coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:30.58,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,CEO Kube...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.92,0:00:32.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.99,0:00:35.09,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine... Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:37.99,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Technology and Research Division 3 told me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.99,0:00:42.77,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,that the Machine Goodfellow trials had started.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.11,0:00:45.39,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,So I thought I'd pay you a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:51.03,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, we're really happy \Nto assist Macbeth Enterprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:53.42,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet your expectations,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.42,0:00:55.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,and repay you for your assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.95,0:00:58.03,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Amara, Moco...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.68,0:01:02.08,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You are special to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:05.17,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Special test pilots...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:10.14,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,But when I say "special," that isn't what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.77,0:01:12.40,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.40,0:01:14.88,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I consider myself not merely your boss,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.39,0:01:17.97,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,but your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.92,0:02:54.15,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,If you need anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.15,0:02:56.62,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,you can always come to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.62,0:02:58.65,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have dinner soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.05,0:03:01.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.42,0:03:09.91,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they good kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.99,0:03:12.87,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad that they were kept
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.87,0:03:17.84,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,at an overseas research organization \Nduring the Kanda incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.79,0:03:20.26,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a good kid, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.25,0:03:25.97,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you invite me to dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:31.27,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we get dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.27,0:03:33.98,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is that an order, Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.64,0:03:37.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's half work, I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.48,0:03:39.74,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't mix work with your personal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.33,0:03:44.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like all the color is \Ndraining from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.65,0:03:49.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's Governor Yomatsuri, from the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.68,0:03:52.71,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.18,0:03:54.00,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.33,0:03:58.50,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Eiji Arashi is still missing, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.00,0:04:00.51,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.03,0:04:02.74,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,This is a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.74,0:04:07.81,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,HQ won't like any issues that \Nmight hinder the Kivotos Plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:12.23,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You tried to get him out without \Npermission, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.45,0:04:15.10,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes look dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.43,0:04:20.12,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Out of consideration for your pathetic face, \Nwe'll just say you owe me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:24.14,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, this conversation is being hacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.14,0:04:24.91,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.36,0:04:30.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Aww. You found me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.25,0:04:31.08,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Akari!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.63,0:04:32.87,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Akari!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:34.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:38.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Dad tried to hit on Rita-san again \Nthis morning, and got rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.95,0:04:41.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You have this room bugged, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:45.21,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, I just took a random guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.97,0:04:51.29,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You're part of Globe now... You work for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:55.89,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Must we go over what you \Ncan and can't do again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:05:00.01,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,How did you get into the secure line, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.01,0:05:02.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Magic! It's magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:04.30,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's forbidden! Magic is forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:10.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what do you guys think \Nabout the Kivotos Plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.77,0:05:18.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That was the plan to enable humanity \Nto escape, should the worst happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.28,0:05:21.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It was deemed necessary by \Nthe unanimous agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.31,0:05:24.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,of all representatives of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.16,0:05:28.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the Globe Federation's \Nunanimous agreement, not humanity's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.91,0:05:34.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If nothing else, I wouldn't want to \Nsurvive thanks to a plan like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.92,0:05:38.15,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The Kivotos Plan is top-secret...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.47,0:05:42.19,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,If you learn any more, I'll have to arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.52,0:05:45.04,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just in the way, anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:48.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Logical, logical... Time for \NAkari-chan to disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:52.16,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Kivotos Plan
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.83,0:05:59.83,Default - italics,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bad mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.06,0:06:09.39,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Alpha sector surveillance footage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:12.34,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Since the battle, the Kiltgang \NType-3 hasn't done anything
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.34,0:06:14.97,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,but float around this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.41,0:06:20.69,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,The Impacter Weinstock is \Ncurrently deployed in that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.69,0:06:21.86,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Keep an eye on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.57,0:06:24.83,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all right not to attack it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.83,0:06:26.57,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,For now, we'll just observe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:29.87,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,That is Globe HQ's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:33.87,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's Globe HQ's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.82,0:06:40.62,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,And his wish, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.03,0:06:43.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But the commander hasn't \Ngranted permission, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.39,0:06:46.38,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He impresses me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.81,0:06:50.33,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, he isn't nearly as good as Teppei,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.33,0:06:52.59,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,but he's already mastered the basic controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.24,0:06:55.35,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been good at these games.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.35,0:06:57.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.70,0:07:02.49,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I think he understands that better than we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.17,0:07:06.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You've only recently joined Globe, \Nso that's enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.69,0:07:08.54,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:10.61,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But she was so worried, \Nshe came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:29.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,After the Kivotos Plan members evacuate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.48,0:07:33.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,the Kiltgang will destroy the \Nremaining people on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:40.29,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And once they're gone, the Kiltgang \Nwill leave the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.29,0:07:41.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:45.05,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They're a kind of space vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.05,0:07:47.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If they require Orgone energy \Non a planetary scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:53.82,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,they're unlikely to remain here \Nafter nearly all humanity dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:57.62,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You are the planet's most \Npowerful electronic brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:07:59.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.73,0:08:01.58,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Puck does not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.05,0:08:06.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I will use this unprecedented threat to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.52,0:08:08.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,to make this planet a utopia,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.57,0:08:12.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,with those people whom I've chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.62,0:08:17.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This whole plot was written \Nfor me by the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:29.44,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tsutomu...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:35.74,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hope means believing that the future \Nwill be better than today...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.08,0:08:40.33,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And real hope can only come \Nfrom the choices you make!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.22,0:09:01.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Toshiaki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.34,0:09:04.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.92,0:09:13.02,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Does your head still hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.02,0:09:14.61,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.99,0:09:18.20,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:22.76,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the first time we met?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.22,0:09:23.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.52,0:09:26.42,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And what you said then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.81,0:09:28.53,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:33.70,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}A voice that resounds throughout infinity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.70,0:09:38.68,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}sings a melody of gentle memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.15,0:09:48.68,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}The light of the promise \NI know we once shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.19,0:09:57.53,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,Is it you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.96,0:10:01.95,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What did that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.92,0:10:07.50,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I've been here for a long time, \Nbut I'm not from this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:12.11,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They created me to fire the Livlaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.82,0:10:16.01,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:19.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,In the distant past...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:24.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I was in a world where everything \Nwas veiled by darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.30,0:10:32.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Darkness surrounded me on all sides,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:37.28,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,and the only thing they wanted \Nme to do was to fire that gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:43.87,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't even sure if I wanted to give \Nthem what they desired or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:48.74,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But then, I thought I saw a light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.19,0:10:55.12,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It felt like someone's voice calling to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.86,0:10:59.47,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that I needed to meet that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.73,0:11:02.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That I wanted to meet that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.34,0:11:24.40,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,So I broke free of their grasp, \Nand ran toward the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:31.23,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the place I ran to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.82,0:11:36.99,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,By "them," do you mean those \NPlanetary Gear guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:41.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,As Planetary Gears, our real \Nbodies are constructed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.68,0:11:44.43,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,from a material called Ego Blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:48.72,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They are crystallized, digitized souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.29,0:11:54.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Unless they're destroyed, \Nwe are theoretically immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.80,0:11:59.18,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We believe that we are the only \Ntrue people in this galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:05.03,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That everyone else is nothing \Nbut a tool for our use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:08.74,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have an Ego Block body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.67,0:12:11.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.56,0:12:15.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I was created as a tool, to fire the Livlaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.55,0:12:19.39,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're not a tool... You're a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.13,0:12:22.97,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.62,0:12:28.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But Teppei's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.23,0:12:33.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei, do you still have your \Npersonality and memories
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:36.86,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,from when you were Albion, \None of the Planetary Gears?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:44.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What does the world look like to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:51.91,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We Planetary Gears might \Nbe like the glass bead
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.91,0:12:54.33,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,in this Ramune soda bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.33,0:12:58.33,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Even when you've drunk it all, \Nand the bottle's job is done,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.33,0:13:00.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,the bead still cannot leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:02.94,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Eternal life...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.42,0:13:06.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Does it mean eternal happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:09.76,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Or is it an eternal prison for the soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.29,0:13:12.92,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:14.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.39,0:13:17.31,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make something good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.31,0:13:20.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What should I make?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.25,0:13:29.24,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,You spend a lot of time alone \Nin the computer room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:33.58,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I like to think by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.98,0:13:36.79,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's my very own sanctuary...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.73,0:13:44.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The lock to that room won't open \Nwithout my biometric data.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.13,0:13:48.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I am the only one who can talk to Puck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:51.23,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This weak security isn't even a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.43,0:13:59.91,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,How have you been, Puck?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.91,0:14:03.79,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Malkin, Amarok.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.38,0:14:08.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Masaki Kube hasn't figured \Nout who we are yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.95,0:14:11.80,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He's a very self-centered man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:15.16,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,That limits what he can see, \Nand makes him easy to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.16,0:14:18.04,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And you have no complaints about life here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.57,0:14:25.26,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,My sole joy in life is being a useful \Ntool to the Planetary Gears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:26.93,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to hear it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.93,0:14:29.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Useful tools will be treated well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.57,0:14:34.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to prove that you're useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:37.33,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I think you understand this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:41.61,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,but her presence is vital to the Kivotos Plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:42.95,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:45.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:47.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put the flower in her vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.10,0:15:09.20,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.42,0:15:12.89,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.79,0:15:25.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Nishikubo-san, I told you to send \NDaichi home immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:27.59,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And you assured me you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.59,0:15:28.19,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.83,0:15:30.95,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me explain things to my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.95,0:15:32.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:34.00,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.00,0:15:36.02,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What does he mean by "Commander"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.02,0:15:37.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Toshiaki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.02,0:15:38.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,He's a minor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.62,0:15:40.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What are you having him do, \Nwithout his guardian's permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:42.25,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:44.96,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone with my uncle for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.76,0:15:48.09,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.88,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Even when your grades fell a bit, \NI wasn't concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:55.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been a good kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:59.15,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't think it's a bad idea \Nfor you to get out and travel
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.15,0:16:01.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,on your own over summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:05.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If it's just a vacation, \Nthere's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.03,0:16:09.03,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're staying on \NTanegashima, that's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.94,0:16:13.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Umi and my brother left me in charge \Nof you, and you're precious to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.01,0:16:16.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And above all, you're my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:23.16,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What you're doing here puts \Nyou in danger, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.98,0:16:26.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.86,0:16:30.05,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really grateful for what you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.70,0:16:32.76,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You've always looked out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:35.95,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.44,0:16:42.88,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,I was in a world where everything \Nwas veiled by darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.15,0:16:48.81,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I felt trapped living in that city, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.26,0:16:54.15,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It always seemed as though it \Nwasn't where I belonged.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:15.85,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.06,0:17:18.47,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,What's dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.98,0:17:22.60,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be enjoying your freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.35,0:17:28.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is the kind of thing that happens \Nwhen you go outside on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:34.24,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I know you aren't certain about \Nwhat to do with your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.40,0:17:37.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Pitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:39.69,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.69,0:17:41.38,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you do that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:47.92,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen to Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.17,0:17:51.88,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.65,0:17:53.54,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.54,0:17:57.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so the Earth Driver has arrived?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:17:58.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.40,0:18:02.51,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,D-Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:03.69,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.42,0:18:05.39,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.54,0:18:07.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.10,0:18:07.81,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.91,0:18:11.36,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:13.82,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.42,0:18:16.86,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take another step.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.32,0:18:19.20,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.95,0:18:21.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking Hana Mutou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:24.62,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is the right choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:31.38,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What is he...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.81,0:18:35.59,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Release Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.21,0:18:39.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you prepared to shoot me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.10,0:18:43.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking if you're prepared to kill someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.71,0:18:48.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:50.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't ready to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.59,0:18:53.40,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And someone like that can't save anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:56.82,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're only a child who happened to get a Livlaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.49,0:19:01.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.91,0:19:02.57,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.14,0:19:09.93,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.85,0:19:12.67,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.42,0:19:19.30,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Right then, I wondered if maybe the voice
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:22.93,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,that had led Hana to this planet was me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.48,0:19:24.25,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.73,0:19:27.06,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted it to be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.85,0:19:33.04,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.05,0:19:35.48,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:37.60,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Toshiaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.01,0:19:39.99,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Nishikubo-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:45.02,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Am I correct that something just happened here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.02,0:19:46.58,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, that it {\i1}will{\i0} happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.39,0:19:50.29,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Something normal people \Nlike me can't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.00,0:19:53.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.59,0:19:55.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.99,0:19:58.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I won't tell anyone what I saw here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:19:59.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Toshiaki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.30,0:20:02.34,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell me one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.96,0:20:07.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is what Daichi is trying to do here \Nsomething that only he can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.89,0:20:09.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.56,0:20:16.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I felt a strength in his words that \NI've never seen in him before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.58,0:20:21.57,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought this day would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.33,0:20:28.73,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,He really is my brother's... \NTaiyou Manatsu's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:36.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Reito Hirosue has been turned over to Salty Dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.03,0:20:41.01,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The Ark Faction is finally starting \Nto get more extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:46.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The Ark Faction wants to ensure \Nthat the Kivotos Plan succeeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:48.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,and that humanity's chosen survive, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.68,0:20:51.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The Interception Faction wants deploy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.02,0:20:53.98,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,the Impacters to defeat the Kiltgangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.45,0:20:57.84,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Globe has supported both plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.84,0:21:00.73,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why do they have to oppose each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.14,0:21:04.45,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're the sub-commander, \NI want to show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.66,0:21:07.66,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.66,0:21:09.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Footage from the dark side of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.18,0:21:11.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Only a few people in Globe,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.99,0:21:15.29,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,and no one in the outside world, can access it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:19.84,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Eight years ago, the mere approach of \Nthe Kiltgang Type-1 sufficed to drain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:23.18,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,the few dozen personnel \Nstationed at the Daedalus base
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.18,0:21:25.30,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,of their libidos, killing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.25,0:21:29.15,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The inexplicable burst phenomenon \Nthat occurred then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.15,0:21:31.63,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,left the dark side of the Moon in this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.87,0:21:37.23,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And this is how the Earth will look \Nafter the Kiltgang attack it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:40.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But among the Intercept Faction, \Nwho believe we can stop them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.07,0:21:42.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,aren't you the most right-wing member?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.29,0:21:44.27,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.85,0:21:48.87,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The Kivotos Plan means the de facto \Nextermination of humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.59,0:21:51.33,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.33,0:21:55.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You said that it can take your \Nlibido simply by getting close.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.57,0:21:59.96,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But Daichi's even fought them at \Nclose range, in the Earth Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.96,0:22:01.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,How did he survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:05.42,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I assume that's the Livlaster's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:09.72,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The gun's Orgone energy seems to protect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:14.99,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But even if Daichi Manatsu can fire the Livlaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.99,0:22:17.94,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,that doesn't change the fact that \Nour situation is near-hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.94,0:22:19.53,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.57,0:22:25.36,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Taiyou...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.60,0:22:29.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You protected Earth and humanity...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.65,0:22:32.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,How can I do the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.01,0:24:17.64,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is humanity already doomed?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.15,0:24:24.52,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is getting a few chosen \Npeople out really our only hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.00,0:24:28.40,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And the Kiltgang attacks Earth again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.53,0:24:31.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But during that battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.09,0:24:35.03,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 7 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:38.01,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:38.20,Title2,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.01,0:24:41.70,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a single hope.
